notes.title: Hello World
notes.body: to be or not to be that is the question whether tis nobler in the mind to suffer the slings and arrows of outrageous fortune or to take arm against a sea fo troubles and by opposing end them to die to sleep noo more and by a sleep to say we end the heartache and the thouse natural shocks that flesh is heir to tis a consummation devoutly to be wishese to die to sleep to sleep perchance to dream ay theres the rub for in that sleeo of death what dreams may come when we have shuffled off this mortal coil must give us pause
